<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="569" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Uhl</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-03"><hi rend="italic">June 3,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the concluding paragraph
                            of Mr. Gresham’s note of April 29 last, and subsequent correspondence, I
                            have the honor to transmit herewith a list of British sealing vessels
                            cleared from Canadian ports for the Bering Sea since November last.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
